	<div class="contentwide">
		<h2>Summary:</h2><div class="infobox">The following cause negative Health:<br /><br />Raw Population: As your civ grows, the people get increasingly less healthy and demand more stuff to improve their lot.<br /><br />Number of Cities: As the number of cities in your colony grows, so does your negative Health. In other words, a colony with two cities each of population 1 is less healthy than a colony with one city of population 2, even though you have the same total population.<br /><br />Annexed Cities: If you capture and annex a foreign City, your population doesn’t like it.<br /><br />Improvements: Certain Improvements, like the Manufactory, can lower the Health of your population.</div>
